NAME
    toggle-dnd-mac

DESCRIPTION
    Control or return status of MacOS system setting for "Do Not Disturb" Mode (toggle/on/off/status) based on passed parameters.

    This function requires 1 [optional] parameter:
        @1 = state

SYNOPSIS
    toggle-dnd-mac state [--dry]
    # Brackets [] indicate optional

EXAMPLES
    toggle-dnd-mac              # <- toggles DND mode (same as `toggle-dnd-mac toggle`)
    toggle-dnd-mac state        # <- returns current DND state ('on' or 'off')
    toggle-dnd-mac on           # <- turns on DND mode
    toggle-dnd-mac off          # <- turns off DND mode
    toggle-dnd-mac off --debug  # <- output the debug info without actually running

AVAILABLE OPTIONS:
    -h, --help                  [output the debug info without actually running]
    -v, --debug               [show this help documentation]
    --status, --get, --current  [return current DND state]
    --on, --enable              [activate/enable DND mode]
    --off, --disable            [deactivate/disable DND mode]
    --toggle                    [toggle DND mode]
